### =============================================================
### AlAshmar API - Flow: Create Survey and Collect Responses
### =============================================================
###
### This file walks through the complete survey lifecycle:
###
###   ADMIN/TEACHER SIDE (run once to set up the survey)
###   Step 1  - Login as admin/manager
###   Step 2  - Create the survey form  (FormType = 0)
###   Step 3  - Add a multiple-choice question
###   Step 4  - Add a checkbox (multi-select) question
###   Step 5  - Add a short-text feedback question
###   Step 6  - Share the survey (get the access token)
###
###   RESPONDENT SIDE — no login required (anonymous access)
###   Step 7  - Fetch the survey via the public access token
###   Step 8  - Fetch questions
###   Step 9  - Fetch options for choice questions
###   Step 10 - Submit a response (student)
###   Step 11 - Submit a response (teacher)
###
###   ADMIN SIDE — Review collected responses
###   Step 12 - View all responses
###   Step 13 - View a specific response
###   Step 14 - Delete a response if needed
###
### Instructions:
###   Run each request in order. After each step that creates a
###   resource, copy the returned "id" / "accessToken" and update
###   the matching variable below.
### =============================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5107

# ── Update these after each step ──────────────────────────────
@adminToken    = YOUR_ADMIN_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

@surveyFormId  = SURVEY_FORM_ID_FROM_STEP_2
@accessToken   = ACCESS_TOKEN_FROM_STEP_2

@q1Id          = QUESTION_1_ID_FROM_STEP_3
@q2Id          = QUESTION_2_ID_FROM_STEP_4
@q3Id          = QUESTION_3_ID_FROM_STEP_5

# Option IDs filled in after Step 9
@q1Option1     = Q1_OPTION_1_ID
@q1Option2     = Q1_OPTION_2_ID
@q1Option3     = Q1_OPTION_3_ID

@q2OptionA     = Q2_OPTION_A_ID
@q2OptionB     = Q2_OPTION_B_ID
@q2OptionC     = Q2_OPTION_C_ID

# Respondent IDs (students/teachers already in the system)
@studentId     = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
@teacherId     = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000011
@managerId     = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000021
@halaqaId      = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000041
@courseId      = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000031

@responseId    = RESPONSE_ID_FROM_STEP_10

# =============================================================
#  ADMIN/TEACHER SIDE — Build the survey
# =============================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 1 - Login as admin/manager
# -----------------------------------------------------------------

### Step 1: Admin login
# Copy the returned "token" into @adminToken above.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "Admin@1234"
}

###

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 2 - Create the survey form
#
#   formType   0  = Normal form / survey  (no auto-grading)
#   formType   1  = Quiz                  (auto-grades)
#   audience   2  = Both students and teachers
#   allowMultipleResponses true = respondent can submit again
# -----------------------------------------------------------------

### Step 2: Create survey
# Copy "id" into @surveyFormId and "accessToken" into @accessToken.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/forms
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "End-of-Month Feedback Survey",
  "description": "Please share your feedback about this month's sessions to help us improve",
  "formType": 0,
  "audience": 2,
  "timerMinutes": null,
  "isActive": true,
  "allowMultipleResponses": false,
  "startsAt": null,
  "endsAt": null,
  "createdByManagerId": "{{managerId}}",
  "halaqaId": "{{halaqaId}}",
  "courseId": "{{courseId}}"
}

###

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 3 - Add a single-select (multiple-choice) question
#   For surveys, "isCorrect" is not meaningful — set all to false.
#   Points is typically null for surveys.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------

### Step 3: Add rating question (multiple-choice)
# Copy the returned "id" into @q1Id above.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/formquestions
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "formId": "{{surveyFormId}}",
  "text": "How would you rate the quality of this month's sessions?",
  "description": "1 = Poor, 5 = Excellent",
  "questionType": 2,
  "order": 1,
  "isRequired": true,
  "points": null,
  "options": [
    {
      "questionId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
      "text": "1 - Poor",
      "order": 1,
      "isCorrect": false
    },
    {
      "questionId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
      "text": "2 - Below Average",
      "order": 2,
      "isCorrect": false
    },
    {
      "questionId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
      "text": "3 - Average",
      "order": 3,
      "isCorrect": false
    },
    {
      "questionId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
      "text": "4 - Good",
      "order": 4,
      "isCorrect": false
    },
    {
      "questionId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
      "text": "5 - Excellent",
      "order": 5,
      "isCorrect": false
    }
  ]
}

###

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 4 - Add a multi-select (checkbox) question
# -----------------------------------------------------------------

### Step 4: Add multi-select question (checkbox)
# Copy the returned "id" into @q2Id above.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/formquestions
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "formId": "{{surveyFormId}}",
  "text": "Which topics would you like to focus on next month? (select all that apply)",
  "description": null,
  "questionType": 3,
  "order": 2,
  "isRequired": true,
  "points": null,
  "options": [
    {
      "questionId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
      "text": "Quran Memorization (Hifz)",
      "order": 1,
      "isCorrect": false
    },
    {
      "questionId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
      "text": "Tajweed Rules",
      "order": 2,
      "isCorrect": false
    },
    {
      "questionId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
      "text": "Hadith Studies",
      "order": 3,
      "isCorrect": false
    },
    {
      "questionId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
      "text": "Islamic History (Seerah)",
      "order": 4,
      "isCorrect": false
    },
    {
      "questionId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
      "text": "Arabic Language",
      "order": 5,
      "isCorrect": false
    }
  ]
}

###

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 5 - Add an open-ended text question
# -----------------------------------------------------------------

### Step 5: Add open-ended feedback question
# Copy the returned "id" into @q3Id above.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/formquestions
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "formId": "{{surveyFormId}}",
  "text": "Do you have any suggestions or comments for the teaching team?",
  "description": "Your feedback helps us improve",
  "questionType": 1,
  "order": 3,
  "isRequired": false,
  "points": null,
  "options": []
}

###

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 6 - Verify the survey is ready
#   Note the "accessToken" in the form response — share this GUID
#   with respondents so they can access the survey anonymously.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------

### Step 6: Get survey to verify + get the access token
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/forms/{{surveyFormId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Step 6b: Get all questions to confirm they were added
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/formquestions/by-form/{{surveyFormId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Accept: application/json

###

# =============================================================
#  RESPONDENT SIDE — Submit a response (anonymous, no login needed)
# =============================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 7 - Fetch the survey via its public access token
#   Normal surveys (FormType=0) allow anonymous access.
#   Only Quiz forms (FormType=1) require authentication.
#   Share this URL with respondents:
#   GET {{baseUrl}}/api/forms/access/<accessToken>
# -----------------------------------------------------------------

### Step 7: Get survey via access token (no auth needed — surveys are anonymous)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/forms/access/{{accessToken}}
Accept: application/json

###

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 8 - Fetch questions for the survey
# -----------------------------------------------------------------

### Step 8: Get survey questions
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/formquestions/by-form/{{surveyFormId}}
Accept: application/json

###

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 9 - Fetch answer options for choice questions
# -----------------------------------------------------------------

### Step 9a: Get options for the rating question
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/formquestionoptions/by-question/{{q1Id}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Step 9b: Get options for the topic preference question
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/formquestionoptions/by-question/{{q2Id}}
Accept: application/json

###

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 10 - Submit a response as a student
#   Surveys (FormType=0) allow anonymous submission — no auth needed.
#   Quiz forms (FormType=1) require authentication at this endpoint.
#   Set respondedByStudentId for student responses.
#   Set respondedByTeacherId for teacher responses.
#   Both can be null for truly anonymous responses.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------

### Step 10: Submit survey response (student)
# Copy the returned "id" into @responseId above.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/formresponses/submit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "formId": "{{surveyFormId}}",
  "respondedByStudentId": "{{studentId}}",
  "respondedByTeacherId": null,
  "timeSpentSeconds": 180,
  "answers": [
    {
      "questionId": "{{q1Id}}",
      "textAnswer": null,
      "selectedOptionIds": ["{{q1Option3}}"]
    },
    {
      "questionId": "{{q2Id}}",
      "textAnswer": null,
      "selectedOptionIds": [
        "{{q2OptionA}}",
        "{{q2OptionB}}"
      ]
    },
    {
      "questionId": "{{q3Id}}",
      "textAnswer": "The sessions are great. Could we have more practice time for memorization?",
      "selectedOptionIds": []
    }
  ]
}

###

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 11 - Submit a response as a teacher
# -----------------------------------------------------------------

### Step 11: Submit survey response (teacher)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/formresponses/submit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "formId": "{{surveyFormId}}",
  "respondedByStudentId": null,
  "respondedByTeacherId": "{{teacherId}}",
  "timeSpentSeconds": 120,
  "answers": [
    {
      "questionId": "{{q1Id}}",
      "textAnswer": null,
      "selectedOptionIds": ["{{q1Option2}}"]
    },
    {
      "questionId": "{{q2Id}}",
      "textAnswer": null,
      "selectedOptionIds": [
        "{{q2OptionA}}",
        "{{q2OptionC}}"
      ]
    },
    {
      "questionId": "{{q3Id}}",
      "textAnswer": "Would appreciate more structured lesson plans and teaching materials.",
      "selectedOptionIds": []
    }
  ]
}

###

# =============================================================
#  ADMIN SIDE — Review collected responses
# =============================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 12 - View all responses for the survey
# -----------------------------------------------------------------

### Step 12: Get all responses for this survey
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/formresponses/by-form/{{surveyFormId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Accept: application/json

###

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 13 - View a specific response in detail
# -----------------------------------------------------------------

### Step 13: Get specific response
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/formresponses/{{responseId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Accept: application/json

###

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 14 - Delete a response if needed
# -----------------------------------------------------------------

### Step 14: Delete a response
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/formresponses/{{responseId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# OPTIONAL - Close the survey when done collecting responses
# -----------------------------------------------------------------

### Optional: Deactivate survey
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/forms/{{surveyFormId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "End-of-Month Feedback Survey",
  "description": "Please share your feedback about this month's sessions to help us improve",
  "formType": 0,
  "audience": 2,
  "timerMinutes": null,
  "isActive": false,
  "allowMultipleResponses": false,
  "startsAt": null,
  "endsAt": null,
  "halaqaId": "{{halaqaId}}",
  "courseId": "{{courseId}}"
}

###
